  "prompt": "How much money is considered to be \"fuck you\" money?",
  "response": "\"Fuck you\" money refers to a level of wealth where one feels financially secure enough to say no to jobs, tasks, or situations they do not want to be involved in, without concern for financial repercussions. The precise amount can vary significantly depending on individual lifestyles, expenses, geographic location, and personal aspirations. For some, it might be a few million dollars, while for others, it could be tens of millions or more. Generally, it is enough to ensure long-term financial independence and security, allowing a person the freedom to live life on their terms.",
